types.section:
{{fr-noun|m}}

# [[saying]] (that which is said)
# [[belief]], [[opinion]]

====Derived terms====
* {{l|fr|aux dires de}}

====Descendants====
* {{desc|lou|di}}

{{fr-verb}}

# {{lb|fr|transitive}} to [[say]], to [[tell]] (to express through speech)
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Fortuné du Boisgobey|title=Double-Blanc|trans-title=Double-Blank|location=Paris|publisher=Plon & Nourrit|year=1889|page=213|text=— Parfaitement... et il '''a dit''' à ces dames que c'était un étranger, arrivé récemment à Paris et colossalement riche.|translation=— Perfectly…and he '''told''' these ladies that he was a foreigner, recently arrived in Paris and colossally rich.}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:H. G. Wells|title=La Guerre dans les airs|original=The War in the Air|origlang=en|origyear=1908|year=1910|page=247|translators=Henry-D. Davray; B. Kozakiewicz|location=Paris|publisher=Mercure de France|edition=1921|text=Bien qu'il n'eût pu comprendre un seul mot de ce qui '''avait été dit''', Bert éprouva un choc en remarquant le ton qu'avait pris l'homme.|translation=Although he could not have understood a single word of that which '''had been said''', Bert felt a shock while noticing the tone that the man had taken.}}
#* {{quote-journal|fr|first=Béatrice|last=Dillies|title=Au vaccinodrome d'Albi : "Emmanuel Macron dit tout haut ce que tout le monde pense tout bas"|trans-title=At the Albi Mass Vaccination Centre: "Emmanuel Macron says out loud what everyone is quietly thinking"|date=January 5, 2022|journal=La Dépêche|url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/2022/01/05/au-vaccinodrome-dalbi-emmanuel-macron-dit-tout-haut-ce-que-tout-le-monde-pense-tout-bas-10028711.php|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20240709190807/https://www.ladepeche.fr/2022/01/05/au-vaccinodrome-dalbi-emmanuel-macron-dit-tout-haut-ce-que-tout-le-monde-pense-tout-bas-10028711.php|archivedate=July 29, 2024|text=Emmanuel Macron aurait dû se mordre la langue avant de parler d'emmerder les récalcitrants. Mais il '''a dit''' tout haut ce que tout le monde pense tout bas.|translation=Emmanuel Macron should have bitten his tongue before talking about bugging the recalcitrants. But he '''said''' out loud what everyone is quietly thinking.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Dire''' qu'on fait des cookies, c'est bien, mais il faut ensuite les partager.|'''To say''' that one is making some cookies, it is good, but it is then necessary to share them.|qualifier=American saying}}
# {{lb|fr|transitive}} to [[tell]] (to order, to advise)
#: {{uxi|fr|Il lui '''a dit''' de partir.|He '''told''' him to go away.}}
# {{lb|fr|transitive}} to say, to tell (to set out in writing)
#: {{uxi|fr|Je vous '''ai dit''' dans ma dernière lettre que….|I '''told''' you in my last letter that….}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Cet auteur '''a dit''' là-dessus d'excellentes choses.|This author '''has said''' some excellent things about it.}}
# {{lb|fr|transitive}} to say (often used in the sense of responding to an objection)
#: {{uxi|fr|Qu'avez-vous à '''dire''' à cela ?|What do you have to '''say''' to that?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Que trouvez-vous à dire à cette action ?|What do you have to '''say''' to this action?|lit=What do you find to '''say''' to this action?|qualifier=in this sense, one more commonly says [[trouver à redire]] {{gloss|to find fault with}}}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Il y a bien à '''dire''', beaucoup à '''dire''' là-dessus.|There is much to '''say''', very much to '''say''' about that.|qualifier=There are a lot of criticisms, of objections, of observations, etc., to make about that.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|On '''dit''' en des sens analogues ou contraires.|One '''says''' in similar or opposite senses.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|On ne peut certainement rien '''dire''' sur sa conduite.|One certainly cannot '''say''' anything about their conduct.}}
# {{lb|fr|transitive|poetic}} to say, to tell of (to celebrate, to sing, to narrate)
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Jean le Rond d'Alembert|title=La Suppression des jésuites (éd. populaire abrégée)|trans-title=The Suppression of the Jesuits (Abridged Popular Ed.)|publisher=Édouard Cornély|year=1888|url=https://fr.m.wikisource.org/wiki/La_Suppression_des_j%C3%A9suites/%C3%A9dition_populaire|text=Il leur offrit de '''dire''' la messe pour leur obtenir de Dieu, au lieu de l'argent qu'ils demandaient, la grâce de souffrir chrétiennement leur ruine.|translation=He offered to '''say''' mass to them to obtain for them from God, instead of the money that they were requesting, the grace to suffer their ruin ''Christianly''.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Je '''dirai''' vos exploits.|I '''will tell of''' your exploits.}}
# {{lb|fr|transitive|current}} to say, to tell (to deliver, to recite)
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Fortuné du Boisgobey|title=Double-Blanc|trans-title=Double-Blank|location=Paris|publisher=Plon & Nourrit|year=1889|page=187|text=C'est bon, je n'aime pas à jouer les gêneurs. Je vais faire un tour au foyer, pendant que tu '''diras''' ton couplet.|translation=It's fine, I don't like to play the nuisance. I'm going to take a walk in the foyer, whilst you '''say''' your verse.}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Jean Rogissart|title=Passantes d'Octobre|trans-title=October Passers-by|location=Paris|publisher=Librairie Arthème Fayard|year=1958|text=Héloïse '''dit''' et redit son chapelet. Les grains cliquettent de minute en minute et sans relâche, le chuchotement rapide des oraisons s'allonge.|translation=Heloise '''says''' and repeats her rosary. The beads clink from minute to minute and relentlessly, the rapid whispers of the orisons get longer.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Dire''' sa leçon.|'''To tell''' one's lesson.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Dire''' la messe.|'''To say''' mass.|qualifier=To celebrate mass}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Faire '''dire''' une messe, des messes pour quelqu'un.|To have a mass or masses '''said''' for someone.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|''Un homme bien-disant'' se '''dit''' d’un Homme qui parle bien et avec facilité.|''A well-spoken man'' is '''said''' of a Man who speaks well and with ease.}}
# {{lb|fr|transitive|figuratively|as the object, with the subject ''on''; often in the conditional}} to seem like, to look like 
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Alexandre Dumas|title=La Reine Margot|trans-title=Queen Margot|year=1845|volume=I|chapter=IV|text=[…] ; sous ses cheveux, un œil gris brillait à la moindre contrariété d'un feu si resplendissant, qu'on '''eût dit''' alors un œil noir.|translation=[…]; under his headhair, a grey eye was shining at the slightest irritation with a fire so gleaming, that it '''seemed to be''' then a black eye.}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Gaston Leroux|title=Le Fantôme de l'Opéra|trans-title=The Phantom of the Opera|year=1910|text=Il semblait, en effet, à tout le monde qu'un frôlement se faisait entendre derrière la porte. Aucun bruit de pas. On '''eût dit''' d'une soie légère qui glissait sur le panneau.|translation=It seemed, indeed, to everyone that a rustling could be heard behind the door. No sounds of footsteps. It '''seemed to be''' a light silk that was sliding along the panel.}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Léon Frapié|title=Les contes de la maternelle|trans-title=Kindergarten Tales|chapter=La croix|trans-chapter=The Cross|publisher=Éditions Self|year=1945|page=29|text=Marie, petite pour ses six ans, les yeux très brillants, la frimousse tendue, presque douloureuse, porte un tablier noir et un minuscule jupon qui laisse voir ses jambes minces, pitoyables. On '''dirait''' d'une poupée tragique.|translation=Marie, small for her six years, her eyes very bright, her cute little face tight, almost painful, wears a black pinafore and a tiny petticoat that lets you see her thin, pitiful legs. She '''looks like''' a tragic doll.}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Angelo Rinaldi|title=Où finira le fleuve|trans-title=Where the River Will End|publisher=Fayard|year=2006|chapter=1|text='''Dirait'''-il que le mouvement de la marche avait révélé la doublure de ce vêtement – était-ce de la castorette ? –, outre une jupe de tweed qui descendait jusqu'au genou ?|translation='''Would''' he '''say''' that the movement of the march had revealed the lining of this garment – was it beaver fur? –, in addition to a tweed skirt that went down to the knee?}}
#* {{quote-journal|fr|author=Marie-Ève Doyon|title=Rire des gros, c'est un manque de classe|trans-title=To Laugh at Overweight People, It Is a Lack of Class|journal=La Journal de Québec|date=December 7, 2021|text=Bien justement. Ce n'est pas parce qu'on peut tout '''dire''' qu'il faut '''dire''' n'importe quoi.|translation=Well exactly. It is not because you can '''say''' anything that it is necessary to '''say''' anything.}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:François Mauriac|title=Le Nœud de vipères|trans-title=The Knot of Vipers|publisher=Éditions Grasset|year=1933|publisher2=Le Livre de Poche|page=23|text=On '''dirait''' d’une main qui se pose sur mon épaule gauche, qui l’immobilise dans une fausse position, comme ferait quelqu’un qui ne voudrait pas que je l’oublie.|translation=It '''feels like''' a hand that is resting on my left shoulder, that immobilizes it in a false position, as someone who would not want me to forget it would do.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|On '''dit''' de même.|It '''seems like''' the same.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|On '''dirait''' de loin une barque; ce n’est peut-être qu’une planche.|It '''looks like''' a small boat from afar; maybe it is not just a plank.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|On '''dirait''' d’un fou, d’un homme ivre, etc., ou On '''dirait''' un fou.|He '''looked like''' a madman, a drunk man, etc.; he '''seemed''' mad/drunk}} (=judging by his actions, by his speech, one would take him for a madman, one would believe him drunk). 
# {{lb|fr|transitive}} to mean, to say, to state (to denote, to signify, to indicate, to mark)
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Julien Gracq|title=Le Rivage des Syrtes|trans-title=The Shore of Sirtes|publisher=José Corti|year=1951|text=La fidélité aux traditions, devenue presque maniaque, '''disait''' l'appauvrissement d'un sang incapable de recréer.|translation=Fidelity to tradition, which had become almost maniacal, '''meant''' the impoverishment of blood unable to recreate.}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:fr:Frédéric Lasaygues|title=Back to la Zone|trans-title=Back to the Zone|location=Paris|publisher=Éditions J'ai Lu|year=1992|text=— Vous êtes au courant de l'arnaque ? C'est l'hypercherie ! L'embrouille totale. Tout est truqué. Silbermann, ça vous '''dit''' quelque chose ? C'est lui le cerveau de la magouille !|translation=— You're in the current of the con? It's the great deception! The total mix-up. Everything is falsified. Silbermann, does that '''mean''' anything to you? It is him the brain of the scheme!}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Edmond Rostand|title=Cyrano de Bergerac|section=Act IV, Scene 4|text=Vous savez ce détail ?… En effet, il advint, / Durant que je faisais ma caracole afin / De rassembler mes gens pour la troisième charge, / Qu'un remous de fuyards m'entraîna sur la marge / Des ennemis ; j'étais en danger qu'on me prît / Et qu'on m'arquebusât, quand j'eus le bon esprit / De dénouer et de laisser couler à terre / L'écharpe qui '''disait''' mon grade militaire ;|translation=You know this detail?… Indeed, it happened, / That while I was making my caracole in order / To assemble my men for the third charge, / That a swirl of fleers drew me onto the fringe / Of the enemy; I was in danger of being captured / And of being arquebused, when I had the good sense / to untie and to let fall to the ground / the scarf that '''stated''' my military rank;}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Que veut '''dire''' ce retard ?|What does this delay '''mean'''?|lit=What does this delay want '''to say'''?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Cela veut '''dire''' que… Cela ne dit rien.|It '''means''' that… It does not say anything.|lit=It wants '''to say''' that… It does not say anything.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Que veut '''dire''' ceci ?|What does this '''mean'''?|lit=What does this want '''to say'''?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Ce mot seul '''dit''' tout.|This word alone '''says''' it all.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Je ne sais ce que cela veut '''dire''', je me sens mal à mon aise.|I do not know what it '''means''', I feel ill at my ease.|lit=I do not know what it wants '''to say''', I feel ill at my ease.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|On '''dit''' : cet homme est un lion, pour '''dire''' que c’est un homme plein de courage.|One '''says''': this man is a lion, to '''mean''' that he is a man full of courage.}}
# {{lb|fr|transitive|figuratively}} to say, to tell (used when speaking of actions, of gestures, of looks, etc., that demonstrate someone's thinking)
#: {{uxi|fr|Mes yeux, mes regards vous '''disent''' que je vous aime.|My eyes, my looks '''tell''' you that I love you.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Sa contenance, son trouble, sa confusion '''disent''' assez qu'il est coupable.|His composure, his trouble, his confusion '''say''' enough that he is guilty.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Leur silence vous en '''dit''' assez, nous en dit long.|Their silence '''tells''' you enough of it, tells us a lot of it.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Cette femme a de beaux yeux, mais ils ne '''disent''' rien.|This woman has beautiful eyes, but they do not '''say''' anything.|qualifier=She has beautiful eyes, but they are devoid of vivacity, of expression.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Cette chose ne '''dit''' rien.|This thing does not '''say''' anything.|qualifier=It does not produce any effect in the place that it occupies.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Cela ne '''dit''' rien au cœur, à l'âme.|It does not '''say''' anything to the heart, to the soul|qualifier=It touches not, moves not.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Cela ne me '''dit''' rien.|It does not '''tell''' me anything.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Qui vous '''dit''', qui vous a '''dit''' que…?|Who '''tells''' you, who '''told''' you that…?|qualifier=What reason do you have to believe that…? Are you sure that…?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Qui vous '''dit''' que j'ai cette intention ?|Who '''tells''' you that I have that intention?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Qui vous a '''dit''' que rien ne s'opposerait à vos desseins ?|Who '''told''' you that nothing would be opposed to your designs?}}
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Georges Feydeau|title=Le Dindon|trans-title=The Turkeycock|year=1896|text=VATELIN. — Ah ! non, ce que ça me '''dit''' ! Ce que ça me '''dit''' !… autant que de me ficher à l'eau !|translation=VATELIN. — Ah! no, what that '''tells''' me! What '''that''' tells me!… may as well thrust myself into the water!}}
# {{lb|fr|transitive|informal}} to call out (to denounce)
#: {{uxi|fr|Aïe ! J'le '''dirai''' !|Ouch! I''''mma call''' him '''out'''!}}
# {{lb|fr|intransitive}} to say (to express what one thinks, what one feels, what one sees)
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Maurice Henrie|title=La tête haute|trans-title=My Head Held High|publisher=University of Ottawa Press|year=2022|page=158|text=Et vous vous réveillez un jour avec ce besoin irrépressible de « dire ».|translation=And you wake up one day with this irrepressible need to "say".}}
# {{lb|fr|reflexive}} to say (to signify, to be used for a word, a phrase, a sentence)
#: {{uxi|fr|Ce mot '''se dit''' de telle chose.|This word '''is said''' of such a thing.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Ce proverbe '''se dit''' en parlant d'une personne qui….|This proverb '''is said''' when speaking of a person who….}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Cela ne '''se dit''' qu'en mauvaise part.|It '''is said''' only in a bad way.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Cela ne '''se dit''' plus.|It '''is''' not '''said''' anymore.}}
# {{lb|fr|reflexive}} to say (to claim, to assure that one has a certain quality)
#: {{uxi|fr|Il '''se dit''' votre parent, votre ami.|He '''says''' he is your relative, your friend.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Il '''se dit''' au courant de ce service et il n'y connaît rien.|He '''says''' he is aware of this service, but he does not know anything about it.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Ils '''se disaient''' envoyés par lui.|They '''said''' they were sent by them.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Il '''se disait''' malade.|He '''said''' he was sick.}}
# {{lb|fr|reflexive|transitive}} to say to oneself, to think to oneself, to tell oneself, to think (to make this or that reflection, to have this or that thought, to make this or that reasoning within oneself)
#* {{quote-book|fr|author=w:Frédéric Weisgerber|title=Trois mois de campagne au Maroc : étude géographique de la région parcourue|trans-title=Three Months of Campaigning in Morocco: A Geographical Study of the Region Covered|location=Paris|editor=Ernest Leroux|year=1904|page=47|text=Ils jettent bien encore des regards de convoitise sur nos bêtes, mais nous nous tenons sur nos gardes, et, nous voyant disposés à nous défendre, ils doivent '''se dire''' que le jeu ne vaudrait peut-être pas la chandelle.|translation=They cast even more glances of covetousness at our beasts, but we stand on our guard, and, seeing us prepared to defend ourselves, they must '''think''' that the game would perhaps not be worth the candle.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Je '''me le disais''' bien, je '''me l’étais bien dit'''.|I '''told myself''' so, I '''told myself''' so.|qualifier=I had a hunch about it.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Quelque chose '''me le dit'''.|Something '''tells me that'''.}}
# {{lb|fr|informal}} to be of [[interest]] to, to [[interest]] {{+obj|fr|:à<someone>}}, to be [[up for]], to be [[interested]], to [[like]] to, to [[feel like]] (to be okay with, to be tempted by)
#: {{uxi|fr|Ça te dit de regarder un film de science-fiction?|Do you want to watch a science fiction movie? [[what do you say|What do you say]] to watching a science fiction movie?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Ça vous dit ?|Are you interested [in doing this]? Are you up [for it]?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Il m'a demandé si ça nous dirait de nous joindre à eux plus tard.|He asked me if we'd like to join them later.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Ça ne me dit trop rien d'y aller.|I don't really want to go [there].}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Ça '''te dirait''' un cinéma ce week-end ?| '''How about''' a movie this weekend?|lit='''Does''' a movie this weekend '''say to you'''?}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Carrément que ça '''me dit''' !|Totally I '''feel like''' it!|lit=Totally it '''says to me'''!}}
# {{lb|fr|informal}} to sound [[familiar]] {{+obj|fr|:à<someone>}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Ça me dit quelque chose.|It [[ring a bell|rings a bell]].}}
#: {{uxi|fr|Ça ne me dit rien.|It doesn't ring a bell.}}

====Conjugation====
{{fr-conj-auto}}
''Disez'' is a nonstandard form for the second person plural in the present indicative.

